<div class="headers  twenty no">
  <h1 style="font-size: 32px;">
  
  
      
        The 11 best Chelsea FC books
        
        
    
    
    </h1>
</div>

<div class="headers  twenty yes">
  
  
  <h3 style="font-size: 20px;">
      
        There are books about Chelsea FC of every description, from autobiographies and annuals to histories and memoirs. We’ve selected our best XI
        
        
    </h3>
    
    
</div>

<div class="basicTextBlock  twenty"><p style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;">Sitting down to select the 11 best Chelsea FC books is not unlike current manager Mauricio Pochettino&rsquo;s job of picking a team from the club&rsquo;s expensively assembled squad.</p>

<p style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;">From a history of the club in headline stories in the personalised <a href="/Product/Arsenal-Football-Headlines---The-Telegraph-Custom-Gift-Book/27331424"><i style="background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:montserrat,sans-serif; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic; font-variant-alternates:normal; font-variant-east-asian:normal; font-variant-numeric:normal; font-variant-position:normal; vertical-align:baseline; white-space-collapse:preserve">Telegraph Custom Gift Book</i></a> (the first name on our teamsheet), to autobiographies of the great Chelsea players and managers and the Official 2024 Annual, readers are spoilt for choice.</p>

<p style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;">But then theirs is a Jekyll-and-Hyde past: rising from the brink of bankruptcy to become the only club to win all three major European trophies twice; sold at different times for &pound;1, &pound;140 million and &pound;2.5 billion; poor underachievers turned rich 21st-century superpower. If these books about Chelsea FC prove anything, it&rsquo;s that their history is a page-turner.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
</div>

</div>
   </div>
</div>
<div class="container-md">
   <div class="row">
      <div class="col-12 listicle-header__wrapper twenty yes">
   <h2 class="listicle-header__header listicle-header__header--center">
      
      The best Chelsea FC history book
      
      
   </h2>
</div>
<div class="basicTextBlock  fourty"><p style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;">These Chelsea FC history books offer different angles on nearly 120 years of football at Stamford Bridge, from how the club&rsquo;s highs and lows have been reported in the Telegraph to the ups and downs of a lifelong love for the team that only true Blues fans feel.</p>
</div>
<div class="col-12 articleList article--center article--underline">
      <div class="article__image-wrapper"><img src="//books.telegraph.co.uk/RichContent/Products/9781472632210/ProductImage/e88a8bf8-f5be-475c-b1d3-060763f600ef_medium.jpg" alt="Chelsea Football Headlines - The Telegraph Custom Gift Book"></div>
      <div class="article__content">
          <div class="article__header">
              <h3><a  href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/Product/Chelsea-Football-Headlines---The-Telegraph-Custom-Gift-Book/27331425">Chelsea Football Headlines - The Telegraph Custom Gift Book</a></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="article__desc">The ultimate Arsenal book. Reproduced articles, match reports and iconic photographs from The Daily Telegraph and The Sunday Telegraph record how the papers have covered the club from 1886. With 13 league titles, a record 14 FA Cup wins and another four major trophies, Arsenal are one of the most successful teams in English football history. This personalised Telegraph Gift Book maps out their story from their formation as Dial Square to the successful eras under Herbert Chapman, George Graham and Arsène Wenger, and their move to the Emirates Stadium after 93 years at Highbury. The perfect Arsenal gift.</div>
          <div class="article__cta"><a  class="button btn" href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/Product/Chelsea-Football-Headlines---The-Telegraph-Custom-Gift-Book/27331425">Read more</a></div>          
      </div>
  </div>
   
  <div class="col-12 articleList article--center article--underline">
      <div class="article__image-wrapper"><img src="//tmg.dmmserver.com/media/356/97818015/9781801504850.jpg" alt="Blue Was the Colour by Andy Hamilton"></div>
      <div class="article__content">
          <div class="article__header">
              <h3><a  href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/Product/Andy-Hamilton/Blue-was-the-Colour--A-Tale-of-Tarnished-Love/28686653">Blue Was the Colour by Andy Hamilton</a></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="article__desc">Comedian and writer Andy Hamilton’s book is subtitled A Tale of Tarnished Love, which gives you a clue that when it comes to Chelsea, his story is something of a bittersweet one. Hamilton grew up in Fulham, near Stamford Bridge, and was taken to his first match at the age of six by his older brother. Love at first sight deepened into an obsession but then the object of his affections changed. Money became the driving force of the modern game, leaving Hamilton, with typically wry humour, to question both his passion for the club and his priorities in life.</div>
          <div class="article__cta"><a  class="button btn" href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/Product/Andy-Hamilton/Blue-was-the-Colour--A-Tale-of-Tarnished-Love/28686653">Read more</a></div>          
      </div>
  </div>
   
  <div class="col-12 articleList article--center ">
      <div class="article__image-wrapper"><img src="//tmg.dmmserver.com/media/356/97817853/9781785316388.jpg" alt="Rhapsody in Blue by Neil Fitzsimon"></div>
      <div class="article__content">
          <div class="article__header">
              <h3><a  href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/Product/Neil-Fitzsimon/Rhapsody-in-Blue--How-I-Fell-in-Love-with-the-Great-Chels/24764401">Rhapsody in Blue by Neil Fitzsimon</a></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="article__desc">The first of Neil Fitzsimon’s trilogy of books about Chelsea FC centres on the team who were regarded as the finest in the first century of the club’s existence. Dave Sexton’s side of the early 1970s won the FA Cup in 1970 and the European Cup-Winners Cup a year later, while also winning admirers for the attractive football they played. Fitzsimon also reflects on what it was like to grow up in the late 1960s, when England were world champions, the decade was still swinging and The Shed and the nearby King’s Road were the places to be.</div>
          <div class="article__cta"><a  class="button btn" href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/Product/Neil-Fitzsimon/Rhapsody-in-Blue--How-I-Fell-in-Love-with-the-Great-Chels/24764401">Read more</a></div>          
      </div>
  </div>
   
  <div class="col-12 articleList article--center ">
      <div class="article__image-wrapper"><img src="//tmg.dmmserver.com/media/356/97818015/9781801503969.jpg" alt="Rebirth Of the Blues by Neil Fitzsimon"></div>
      <div class="article__content">
          <div class="article__header">
              <h3><a  href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/Product/Neil-Fitzsimon/Rebirth-of-the-Blues--The-Rise-of-Chelsea-Football-Club-in-the-Mid-1980s/27604269">Rebirth Of the Blues by Neil Fitzsimon</a></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="article__desc">The concluding part of Fitzsimon’s trilogy charts the beginning of the club’s recovery from the financial problems that had brought it to its knees in the 1970s. Again, his personal account is part Chelsea history book, part social history he evokes the changing political landscape of Thatcherite Britain. Against this backdrop, Chelsea, having narrowly avoided relegation to the old Third Division, appoint John Neal as manager and he builds a team spearheaded by the forward trio Kerry Dixon, David Speedie and Pat Nevin that make a triumphant return to the top flight and drag the club out of the doldrums.</div>
          <div class="article__cta"><a  class="button btn" href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/Product/Neil-Fitzsimon/Rebirth-of-the-Blues--The-Rise-of-Chelsea-Football-Club-in-the-Mid-1980s/27604269">Read more</a></div>          
      </div>
  </div>
   
  <div class="col-12 articleList article--center article--underline">
      <div class="article__image-wrapper"><img src="//tmg.dmmserver.com/media/356/97819091/9781909178502.jpg" alt="Chelsea on This Day by Mike Donovan"></div>
      <div class="article__content">
          <div class="article__header">
              <h3><a  href="https://www.amazon.co.uk/Chelsea-This-Day-History-Figures/dp/1909178500">Chelsea on This Day by Mike Donovan</a></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="article__desc">Mike Donovan’s contribution to the canon of Chelsea FC history books reminds us that following a football team is a full-time job. He has compiled History, Facts & Figures From Every Day of the Year – a diary with a difference for true Blues obsessives. These pages pinpoint all the key events – from the day the club was sold to Ken Bates for one English pound to the day Bates sold it to Roman Abramovich for a few petrodollars more – and will also tell you exactly when 1,001 other memorable moments in their history took place.</div>
          <div class="article__cta"><a  class="button btn" href="https://www.amazon.co.uk/Chelsea-This-Day-History-Figures/dp/1909178500">Read more</a></div>          
      </div>
  </div>
   
  <div class="col-12 listicle-header__wrapper twenty yes">
   <h2 class="listicle-header__header listicle-header__header--">
      
      Chelsea books – autobiographies 
      
      
   </h2>
</div>
<div class="basicTextBlock  fourty"><p style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;">These stories of the men who have been there, done that and worn the shirt make some of the best books about Chelsea FC, include a serial winner to two wingers in the same 1980s team who experienced adulation and the polar opposite from the club&rsquo;s supporters.</p>
</div>
<div class="col-12 articleList article--center article--underline">
      <div class="article__image-wrapper"><img src="//tmg.dmmserver.com/media/356/97819131/9781913183387.jpg" alt="The Accidental Footballer by Pat Nevin"></div>
      <div class="article__content">
          <div class="article__header">
              <h3><a  href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/Product/Pat-Nevin/The-Accidental-Footballer/25432696">The Accidental Footballer by Pat Nevin</a></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="article__desc">Former Chelsea winger Pat Nevin has written a very different kind of Chelsea FC book. The Scot looked destined for teaching rather than football but proved too talented to escape the attention of the football scouts in his native Glasgow. Even after Chelsea lured him away from Clyde in 1983, he was a world apart from most players – a lover of music and the arts who spoke out in public against the racism and violence that blighted the game in the 1980s and 90s. In his memoir, he tells the story of his career with honesty and humour.</div>
          <div class="article__cta"><a  class="button btn" href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/Product/Pat-Nevin/The-Accidental-Footballer/25432696">Read more</a></div>          
      </div>
  </div>
   
  <div class="col-12 articleList article--center article--underline">
      <div class="article__image-wrapper"><img src="//tmg.dmmserver.com/media/356/97818015/9781801500098.jpg" alt="Always Believe by Olivier Giroud"></div>
      <div class="article__content">
          <div class="article__header">
              <h3><a  href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/Product/Olivier-Giroud/Always-Believe--The-Autobiography-of-Olivier-Giroud/25797086">Always Believe by Olivier Giroud</a></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="article__desc">In three and a half seasons at Stamford Bridge, Olivier Giroud won the Champions League, Europa League, FA Cup and – in another shade of blue – the 2018 World Cup with France. His autobiography is more than just a Chelsea FC book but he admits that winning ‘the big titles’ with the Blues was a special time for him. He traces his journey from the fifth tier of French football with Grenoble, to Montpellier and the Premier League with Arsenal, and speaks with candour about life in the spotlight and the constant criticism that came with his selection for the national side.</div>
          <div class="article__cta"><a  class="button btn" href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/Product/Olivier-Giroud/Always-Believe--The-Autobiography-of-Olivier-Giroud/25797086">Read more</a></div>          
      </div>
  </div>
   
  <div class="col-12 articleList article--center article--underline">
      <div class="article__image-wrapper"><img src="//tmg.dmmserver.com/media/356/97802412/9780241244944.jpg" alt="Quiet Leadership by Carlo Ancelotti"></div>
      <div class="article__content">
          <div class="article__header">
              <h3><a  href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/Product/Carlo-Ancelotti/Quiet-Leadership--Winning-Hearts-Minds-and-Matches/20430285">Quiet Leadership by Carlo Ancelotti</a></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="article__desc">No book about Chelsea FC can omit Carlo Ancelotti, the manager who led them to their first domestic double of Premier League and FA Cup in 2009-10. His own autobiography is subtitled Winning Hearts, Minds and Matches – and it is to the Italian’s great credit he has completed that particular treble pretty much everywhere he has worked. He explains how building team cultures and relationships have inspired his success at Milan, PSG, Chelsea, Bayern Munich and Real Madrid, among others. Next he will be the first overseas coach of the Brazil national team since 1965. Another chapter in the making.</div>
          <div class="article__cta"><a  class="button btn" href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/Product/Carlo-Ancelotti/Quiet-Leadership--Winning-Hearts-Minds-and-Matches/20430285">Read more</a></div>          
      </div>
  </div>
   
  <div class="col-12 articleList article--center article--underline">
      <div class="article__image-wrapper"><img src="//tmg.dmmserver.com/media/356/97807553/9780755316458.jpg" alt="Black and Blue by Paul Canoville"></div>
      <div class="article__content">
          <div class="article__header">
              <h3><a  href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/Product/Paul-Canoville/Black-and-Blue--How-Racism-Drugs-and-Cancer-Almost-Destroyed-Me/21000157">Black and Blue by Paul Canoville</a></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="article__desc">Former winger Paul Canoville’s autobiography, perhaps uniquely among books about Chelsea, is both a reminder of one of football’s bleakest eras and a story of hope. Canoville became the club’s first black player when he made his debut at Crystal Palace in 1982, but a proud day was tainted when he was loudly booed by racists among the Chelsea support. Yet extreme bigotry is just one battle he has faced, along with a career-ending injury, drug addiction, family tragedy and two life-threatening bouts of lymph cancer. However, for all those experiences, he remains a positive person – and a Chelsea fan.</div>
          <div class="article__cta"><a  class="button btn" href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/Product/Paul-Canoville/Black-and-Blue--How-Racism-Drugs-and-Cancer-Almost-Destroyed-Me/21000157">Read more</a></div>          
      </div>
  </div>
   
  <div class="col-12 listicle-header__wrapper twenty yes">
   <h2 class="listicle-header__header listicle-header__header--center">
      
      Chelsea trivia books
      
      
   </h2>
</div>
<div class="basicTextBlock padding fourty"><p style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;">And finally&hellip; two books about Chelsea FC that will either bring back memories of the club&rsquo;s past or have you scratching your head trying to answer questions about it, from the official annual to a list of top tens to conclude our first XI.&nbsp;</p>
</div>
<div class="col-12 articleList article--center article--underline">
      <div class="article__image-wrapper"><img src="https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/71abQoZdvUL._SL1500_.jpg" alt="The Official Chelsea Annual 2024"></div>
      <div class="article__content">
          <div class="article__header">
              <h3><a  href="https://www.amazon.co.uk/Official-Chelsea-FC-Annual-2024/dp/1915879159/ref=sr_1_1?crid=V0OLNWKE46N1&keywords=chelsea+annual&qid=1702557181&s=books&sprefix=chelsea+annual%2Cstripbooks%2C79&sr=1-1">The Official Chelsea Annual 2024</a></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="article__desc">When it comes to the best books about Chelsea FC for young Blues supporters, this one is unbeatable. There are exclusive interviews and player profiles featuring the cream of the men’s and women’s teams, such as World Cup winner Enzo Fernandez, super striker Sam Kerr, plus siblings Reece and Lauren James. As befits the only London club ever to win the men’s Champions League, there’s plenty about the club’s past glories. There’s also inside information on some of Stamford Bridge’s stars of the future, plus plenty of puzzles and quizzes to test the knowledge of the most devoted Chelsea fan.</div>
          <div class="article__cta"><a  class="button btn" href="https://www.amazon.co.uk/Official-Chelsea-FC-Annual-2024/dp/1915879159/ref=sr_1_1?crid=V0OLNWKE46N1&keywords=chelsea+annual&qid=1702557181&s=books&sprefix=chelsea+annual%2Cstripbooks%2C79&sr=1-1">Read more</a></div>          
      </div>
  </div>
   
  <div class="col-12 articleList article--center article--underline">
      <div class="article__image-wrapper"><img src="//tmg.dmmserver.com/media/356/97817853/9781785318610.jpg" alt="The Top Ten of Everything Chelsea"></div>
      <div class="article__content">
          <div class="article__header">
              <h3><a  href="https://www.amazon.co.uk/Top-Ten-Everything-Chelsea-Azpilicueta/dp/1785318616/ref=sr_1_1?crid=2KM3GJOPPVWO8&keywords=The+Top+Ten+of+Everything+Chelsea&qid=1702556943&s=books&sprefix=the+top+ten+of+everything+chelsea+%2Cstripbooks%2C101&sr=1-1">The Top Ten of Everything Chelsea</a></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="article__desc">As sure as football is a game of opinions, this is the best Chelsea FC book to get the ball rolling and start a debate about the club. Subtitled The Best of the Blues from Azpilicueta to Zola, compiler Clive Batty’s compendium of trivia, facts and stats covers pretty much all the categories you could imagine. There’s no surprise about seeing lists of silverware and skippers – or players, managers and memorable moments. But fans will have great fun with more left-field entries such as players’ tattoos, terrace chants from The Shed and lists of the club’s best and worst kits.</div>
          <div class="article__cta"><a  class="button btn" href="https://www.amazon.co.uk/Top-Ten-Everything-Chelsea-Azpilicueta/dp/1785318616/ref=sr_1_1?crid=2KM3GJOPPVWO8&keywords=The+Top+Ten+of+Everything+Chelsea&qid=1702556943&s=books&sprefix=the+top+ten+of+everything+chelsea+%2Cstripbooks%2C101&sr=1-1">Read more </a></div>          
      </div>
  </div>
   
  
   </div>
</div>
